Metrics Calculation
Elaborate Explanation:
  df['ctr'] = df['clicks'] / df['impressions'] * 100: Vectorized division/percentage—handles all rows instantly.
  Similarly for cpc, cpa, roi (ROI uses assumed $200 conversion value: revenue - cost / cost).
  print(df[['platform', ...]].round(2)): Selective rounded table output .
Code Explanation: Adds columns for CTR (clicks / impressions * 100), CPC (spend / clicks), CPA (spend / conversions), and ROI ((conversions * 200 - spend) / spend * 100). Rounds and prints a summary table focused on key columns. These are standard ad KPIs used in industry tools like Google Analytics
Advantages: Pandas efficiency (1M+ rows/sec); industry-standard formulas integrable with tools like Google Analytics; automates manual Excel work.
Disadvantages: NaN errors on zero-divides; simplistic ROI (ignores multi-channel attribution); fixed assumptions.
Future Help: Core for marketing dashboards (e.g., Tableau jobs); extends to cohort analysis/churn prediction, boosting resumes for growth marketing roles.
