Code Explanation: Prepares features (impressions, clicks) and target (conversions); splits data (70/30 train/test); fits LinearRegression, predicts on test set, and evaluates with MSE. Outputs error and predictions. Models linear relationship: more impressions/clicks → more conversions .
Advantages: Fast prototyping (seconds to insights); interpretable (coefficients show feature impact); baseline for advanced ML.
Disadvantages: Small data → poor generalization; linear bias (ads saturate); no feature engineering/cross-validation.
Future Help: Entry to predictive analytics (e.g., churn forecasting); Scikit-learn proficiency leads to senior ML roles in adtech (e.g., Facebook); upgrade to XGBoost/time-series

